quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  14,13,"The unbelievers said to their Messengers, 'We will assuredly expel you from our land, or you will surely return into our creed.' Then did their Lord reveal unto them: 'We will surely destroy the evildoers"
  14,14,"and We will surely make you to dwell in the land after them -- that, for him who fears My station and fears My threat"
  14,15,They sought a judgment; then was disappointed every froward tyrant
  14,16,"beyond him Gehenna, and he is given to drink of oozing pus"
  14,17,"the which he gulps, and can scarce swallow, and death comes upon him from every side, yet he cannot die; and still beyond him is a harsh chastisement"
  14,18,"The likeness of those who disbelieve in their Lord: their works are as ashes, whereon the wind blows strong upon a tempestuous day; they have no power over that they have earned - that is the far error"
  14,19,"Hast thou not seen that God created the heavens and the earth in truth? If He will, He can put you away and bring a new creation"
  14,20,that is surely no great matter for God
  14,21,"They sally forth unto God, all together; then say the weak to those who waxed proud, 'We were your followers; will you avail us against the chastisement of God anything?' They say, 'If God had guided us, we would have guided you. Alike it is for us whether we cannot endure, or whether we are patient; we have no asylum"